クリスマスになると思い出す短大時代、菅沼真砂子先生による児童文学期末試験の問題。「あなたは、サンタクロースはいると思いますか？」当時の私には、衝撃的な問いでした。こういった様々な問いによって、自分はどう考えるのか、しっかりとしたものを持ちなさいと鍛えて下さった青短は、人間的に魅力溢れる先生がたくさんいらっしゃいました。そんな大人たちに出会えたことは、私にとって大きな財産となっています。素敵な大人と一杯出会おう♪
「サンタクロースはいると思いますか？」素晴らしい問いですね♪　良い先生との出会いは一生の宝だと、最近実感しています。

It's "a shame" Russell Wilson plays in Seattle? You "get lost in the Pacific Northwest"? The Seahawks media market is bigger than that of Indy, Denver, KC, Jacksonville, Tennessee, Pittsburgh, Cincy, Cleveland...
It's a shame Kevin Durant played in Seattle, too. Good thing he plays in a powerhouse media market now.
I think it has more to do with time zones than anything.
But the NW is not a great football area. Unlike Indy, KC and others we have other things to do.

Pacific time zone has 50 million people, which includes the LA market that doesn't even have a football team. I just bristle at the argument that our region don't deserve good athletes (or other things like concert tour stops) just because we're in the upper left corner of the US.
It was such a stupid comment.
